freetext.HEALTHCARE_VISITS_OTHER: I had a video appointment with a PA from my PCPs office, yesterday.  Today, I communicated via messages to have the After Visit notes corrected.
freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: I started a short course of Prednisone to calm my reaction to poison oak down. I realize that this may impact the efficacy of the vaccine. Meanwhile, the area around my right eye is no longer puffy, but my left hand is puffy.  This is the hand on the side of both the shot and the most extreme reaction to poison oak on my forearm.

freetext.HEALTHCARE_VISITS_OTHER: See prior notes about video visit early this week with PA. In approx. a month we may test my antibodies to make sure that the Prednisone did not obliterate my immunity to CoViD19.
freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Rash on left forearm is scabbing over, with new rash at fringes. Reminder that this was probably poison oak from exposure over a week ago. Using Prednisone at modest level & now reducing dosage each day. Small patches of itchy red rash have shown up on right arm, lower left abdomen, &  left thigh. The area around the right eye is no longer swollen & the swelling on the left hand and arm has reduced. Itchy rash on right jaw is now just a little rough skin, & returning to normal.

freetext.HEALTHCARE_VISITS_OTHER: Video conference with a PA earlier this week.
freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Left hand is swollen. Poison oak rash is mostly healing, with a little new rash showing up on same arm as injection, as well as elsewhere. The area around my right eye is now fine. The prednisone has helped, but I realize that it reduces the efficacy of the vaccine, so being minimal with a modest dose that is fairly short in duration, tapering off over the next four or five days.
Poison oak rash on same arm as vaccine is weeping. Puffy and red around the right eye, opposite side of the poison oak rash.
Swelling around right eye. Lower left arm is red, with weeping water blisters.  This is most likely from exposure to poison oak, last week

The rash on my left forearm is healing and my hand isnt longer swollen. Small new poison oak rashes have shown up, but they are minor compared to the area on my forearm that is now scabbing and healing.
rash may be poison oak... same arm, but lower and inside from wrist up four inches
